The eFamily of channels on DStv is expanding, with the launch of eBella. The new channel will come online on 5 March and will be broadcast on DStv channel 159. It offers a mix of “local and international content inspired by women from across the world”. “eBella is a female-centered channel reflecting the lives and stories of women around the world,” said the company. The channel will feature international telenovelas, including Qubool Hai and Fatmagul. eBella will be available to DStv Premium, Compact Plus, Compact, Family, and Access customers in South Africa.